Citation.sTitle: Experimental solid-liquid equilibria of the ternary system Co(NO3)2 + Mn(NO3)2 + H2O at 20 .deg.C, 0 .deg.C and -15 .deg.C
Citation.sAbstract: The solid-liquid equilibrium (SLE) phase diagram for the ternary systems of (water + cobalt nitrate + manganese nitrate) was experimentally determined via a method based on conductivity measurements under atmospheric pressure. Three isotherms were established at 20 .deg.C, 0 .deg.C and -15 .deg.C. The characterization of solid phases formed in the three isotherms was conducted using atomic absorption spectroscopy (AAS) and X-ray diffraction (XRD), and was confirmed using chemical analysis. Three stable solid phases were identified in these isotherms are: ice, manganese nitrate hexahydrate Mn(NO3)2*6H2O and Cobalt nitrate hexahydrate Co(NO3)2*6H2O.
